To install MMBase richtext:

- You need a servlet 2.4 application server like Tomcat 5. Youre web.xml must be version 2.4 (to
   enable EL)
- You need MMBase 1.8, complete with the shipped jstl.jar and standard.jar

then:

- Place from web-app/WEB-INF/lib  mmbase-richtext.jar, kupu-i18n.jar and mmbase-kupu-i18n.jar in
   your WEB-INF/lib.
- Copy everyting from the directory /mmbase. It contains a directory 'kupu' and one css in mmbase/style/css.
- (Re)start MMBase.

The install the demo:

- Copy the directory web-app/templates, e.g. to <your web-app>/richtext
- Use your browser to see the index.jspx and read it.


Michiel Meeuwissen <richtext@meeuw.org>
